<Content>Looks can be deceiving We checked in our room about 10:00 pm on a Saturday night and were ready to go to bed. WELL my husband pulled back the covers and lo and behold there is hair in the bed and not just one, the sheets had OBVIOUSLY not been changed and so we checked the other bed (room w/two queens) and it to had NOT been changed. We called the front desk and they sent someone to our room to see. They did give us another room but no other compensation. But was told by the guy who took us to the other room I did pull back the covers and there was only an eye lash and kind of chuckled. My view is They should not have to check the bedding it should automatically be changed no matter what! 
