<Author>Cap_nCrunch
<Content>Good Value for Your Money Microtel Plano is a clean, comfortable, basic hotel. It has a Preston Road address but is set back from Preston Road and a little hard to find. Going south on Preston Road, just past the exits from George Bush Turnpike, turn right at Silver Star Motorcars. Follow the road which has a wall on the right.The bed was comfortable and the in-wall air conditioner and heating unit worked well. In-wall units tend to be noisy, in my opinion, and I would judge the noise about average for this type of unit. The continental breakfast offered coffee, juice, cereal and bagels, but no donuts or pastries. The phone service included free local and long distance calls with excellent voice quality. The free high speed wireless internet access worked well from my laptop computer. The TV system offered a good selection of local and cable channels but not a full lineup of extended basic cable channels.I would recommend Microtel Plano to guests looking for a good basic budget hotel. 
